                "Ethnographic Background: The Province and the City of IspartaEthnography of Rose Production and Rose Oil Industry; Contemporary Issues in Rose Oil Production; Rose Oil Industry and Price Formation; Concluding Discussion: The Moral Dimension and Just Prices in the Rose Oil Economy; Notes; Acknowledgments; References; What's in a Just Price? Challenging Values at an Organic Cooperative in Southern Spain; Introduction; La Verde: A Political Project in Cadiz Province, Andalusia; La Verde: Values and Just Prices; Worlds without Money?; To Market, to Market; The Andalusian Context; Conclusion",
                "Front Cover; The Politics and Ethics of The Just Price: Ethnographies of Market Exchange; Copyright Page; Contents; List of Tables; Volume Editor Biographies; Contributor Biographies; Foreword; Introduction -- Toward an Anthropology of the Just Price: History, Ethnography, and Critique; Introduction; In Search of the Just Price; Aristotle and the Problem of Commensuration; The Just Price as Market Value; The Just Price as Labor Value; The Just Price as Social Value; The Paradox of the Just Price; Toward an Anthropology of the Just Price; Conclusion; Notes; References",
